### Step 6: Create Questions

#### Question 1: Explain Closure

```sql
INSERT INTO questions (
    ID, TITLE, SLUG, SUMMARY, CONTENT_HTML, SOLUTION_MD, 
    DIFFICULTY, STATUS, VIEWS, CREATED_BY, CREATED_AT
)
VALUES (
    1,
    'Explain Closure in JavaScript',
    'explain-closure-in-javascript',
    'What is a closure and how does it work?',
    '<h2>What is a Closure?</h2><p>A closure is a function that has access to variables in its outer scope...</p>',
    '# Solution\n\nA closure is created when:\n1. A function is defined inside another function\n2. The inner function accesses variables from the outer function\n\n```javascript\nfunction outer() {\n  let count = 0;\n  return function inner() {\n    count++;\n    return count;\n  }\n}\n```',
    'MEDIUM',
    'PUBLISHED',
    127,  -- 127 views
    1,    -- Created by admin user
    NOW()
);
```

#### Question 2: Async/Await

```sql
INSERT INTO questions (
    ID, TITLE, SLUG, SUMMARY, CONTENT_HTML, SOLUTION_MD, 
    DIFFICULTY, STATUS, VIEWS, CREATED_BY, CREATED_AT
)
VALUES (
    2,
    'What is async/await in JavaScript?',
    'what-is-async-await-in-javascript',
    'Explain how async/await works and when to use it',
    '<h2>Async/Await</h2><p>Async/await is syntactic sugar over Promises...</p>',
    '# Solution\n\n`async/await` makes asynchronous code look synchronous...\n\n```javascript\nasync function fetchData() {\n  const data = await fetch("/api/data");\n  return data.json();\n}\n```',
    'EASY',
    'PUBLISHED',
    89,
    1,
    NOW()
);
```

#### Question 3: Promises (Draft)

```sql
INSERT INTO questions (
    ID, TITLE, SLUG, SUMMARY, CONTENT_HTML, SOLUTION_MD, 
    DIFFICULTY, STATUS, VIEWS, CREATED_BY, CREATED_AT
)
VALUES (
    3,
    'How do Promises work?',
    'how-do-promises-work',
    'Understanding the Promise API',
    '<h2>Promises</h2><p>A Promise represents a future value...</p>',
    '# Solution\n\nPromises have three states: pending, fulfilled, rejected...',
    'HARD',
    'DRAFT',  -- Not published yet!
    0,
    1,
    NOW()
);
```

**Questions table result:**
```
+----+----------------------------------+------------------------------------+----------+----------+-------+------------+
| ID | TITLE                            | SLUG                               | DIFFICULTY| STATUS   | VIEWS | CREATED_BY |
+----+----------------------------------+------------------------------------+----------+----------+-------+------------+
|  1 | Explain Closure in JavaScript    | explain-closure-in-javascript      | MEDIUM   | PUBLISHED|   127 |          1 |
|  2 | What is async/await in JavaScript| what-is-async-await-in-javascript  | EASY     | PUBLISHED|    89 |          1 |
|  3 | How do Promises work?            | how-do-promises-work               | HARD     | DRAFT    |     0 |          1 |
+----+----------------------------------+------------------------------------+----------+----------+-------+------------+
```

